Note:
Decimal Bignum - shared multi-digit decimal helpers used by the IEEE
754-2008 Decimal64, Decimal128, and arbitrary-precision decimal modules.

The single Integer in the bootstrap stage1 holds at most 18 decimal digits
(2^63 - 1 = 9223372036854775807). Decimal64 (16 digits) products produce
32-digit intermediates, Decimal128 (34 digits) needs 34-digit coefficients
plus 68-digit products. Both cases exceed Integer range.

This module exposes a "digit buffer" abstraction:

    digit_buffer = pointer to a byte array where each byte holds one
                   decimal digit 0..9 (NOT ASCII; raw 0..9 values).
                   index 0 = MOST SIGNIFICANT digit (big-endian).

    A digit_buffer is always paired with an Integer "digit count" that
    indicates how many of the leading bytes hold valid digits. Bytes
    beyond digit_count are unspecified.

All routines in this module take ownership semantics from their callers:
the caller allocates digit buffers via decbn_alloc and releases them via
decbn_free. Functions that return a new buffer document the allocation
in their @Reasoning block.

IEEE 754-2008 conformance: the routines here implement the integer-domain
primitives used by Section 5 operations. They do not enforce any precision
constraint themselves; the calling Decimal{32,64,128} module is responsible
for capping the result to its precision via decbn_round_to_precision.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Rounding mode constants - shared with all Decimal modules.
Note: ============================================================================

Constant DECBN_ROUND_HALF_EVEN as Integer is 0
Constant DECBN_ROUND_HALF_UP as Integer is 1
Constant DECBN_ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO as Integer is 2
Constant DECBN_ROUND_TOWARD_POS as Integer is 3
Constant DECBN_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG as Integer is 4

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Allocator
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "decbn_alloc" takes capacity as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates a zero-initialized digit buffer with the requested byte
    capacity. The Layout.allocate path guarantees zero-initialized
    pages per the calloc-zero contract documented in
    memory/layout.runa allocate(), so we do not need an explicit
    fill.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Layout.allocate; if it returns 0 we propagate the 0 sentinel.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) at the allocator level. Hot path for arithmetic intermediates.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure propagates as 0 (NULL). Callers MUST check.
    @End Security_Scope

    If capacity is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Layout.allocate(capacity)
End Process

Process called "decbn_free" takes buf as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Releases a digit buffer allocated via decbn_alloc. Idempotent on
    NULL via the underlying allocator.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Layout.deallocate.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Double-free triggers the canary protocol in the allocator.
    @End Security_Scope

    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Layout.deallocate(buf)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Conversion: Integer <-> digit buffer
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "decbn_from_integer" takes value as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Converts a non-negative Integer to a freshly-allocated digit buffer
    with the most-significant digit at index 0. The digit count is
    written into the Integer at out_count_ptr (offset 0). The returned
    buffer is sized to the actual digit count plus one byte of slack
    for in-place carry propagation by downstream routines.

    For value = 0 we still return a 1-digit buffer holding 0 because
    that is the conventional representation of zero.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Compute digit count via successive division by 10.
    2. Allocate buffer.
    3. Fill from the right (least significant) up.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(log10 value). The 2-pass form (count then fill) avoids reallocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Negative input is treated as its absolute value; the caller must
    track the sign separately. out_count_ptr must point to writable
    Integer storage.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let v be value
    If v is less than 0:
        Set v to 0 minus v
    End If
    Let count be 0
    If v is equal to 0:
        Set count to 1
    Otherwise:
        Let scan be v
        While scan is greater than 0:
            Set count to count plus 1
            Set scan to scan divided by 10
        End While
    End If

    Let buf be decbn_alloc(count plus 1)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    If v is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, 0, 0)
    Otherwise:
        Let idx be count minus 1
        Let cur be v
        While cur is greater than 0:
            Let digit be cur minus ((cur divided by 10) multiplied by 10)
            Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, idx, digit)
            Set cur to cur divided by 10
            Set idx to idx minus 1
        End While
    End If

    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, count)
    End If
    Return buf
End Process

Process called "decbn_to_integer_capped" takes buf as Integer, count as Integer, cap_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads the first cap_digits leading digits of buf and packs them
    into a single Integer. If count < cap_digits the value is whatever
    digits exist; if count > cap_digits the lower digits are discarded
    (use decbn_round_to_precision first if rounding is desired).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Accumulator * 10 + digit, bounded to cap_digits iterations.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(cap_digits) which is bounded by 18 (the Integer limit).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    cap_digits must be <= 18 to avoid Integer overflow. Callers in this
    module enforce that constraint.
    @End Security_Scope

    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If count is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let limit be cap_digits
    If limit is greater than count:
        Set limit to count
    End If
    Let result be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than limit:
        Let d be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, i)
        Set result to (result multiplied by 10) plus d
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return result
End Process

Process called "decbn_copy" takes src as Integer, src_count as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates a new buffer and copies the leading src_count digits.
    The new buffer has one byte of slack for downstream carry
    propagation, matching decbn_from_integer.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    decbn_alloc + memory_copy via a digit loop (avoids dependence on
    memory_copy which is overkill for typical 16-34 digit counts).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(src_count). Inline copy loop avoids a function-call boundary.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If src is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If src_count is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let buf be decbn_alloc(src_count plus 1)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than src_count:
        Let d be Memory.memory_get_byte(src, i)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, i, d)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return buf
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Comparison
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "decbn_compare_magnitude" takes a as Integer, a_count as Integer, b as Integer, b_count as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Magnitude compare: returns -1, 0, or 1. Leading zeros are NOT
    handled here; callers must pass normalized counts (no leading
    zeros) for the comparison to be correct. The reason we do not
    auto-strip leading zeros is that strip would require scanning
    both buffers, doubling the cost in the hot path; the calling
    arithmetic routines always produce normalized counts already.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Strip leading zeros locally (cheap; in normalized inputs the
       strip is a no-op).
    2. Compare effective digit counts.
    3. If equal, compare digit-by-digit from MSD to LSD.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(min(a_count, b_count)) in the worst case (equal magnitudes).
    Best case O(1) when lengths differ.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure. NULL inputs treated as zero magnitude.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_eff be a_count
    Let b_eff be b_count
    Note: Skip leading zeros to ensure correct length comparison.
    Let ai be 0
    Let a_scanning be 1
    While a_scanning is equal to 1:
        If ai is greater than or equal to a_eff:
            Set a_scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            If a is equal to 0:
                Set a_eff to 0
                Set a_scanning to 0
            Otherwise:
                Let av be Memory.memory_get_byte(a, ai)
                If av is equal to 0:
                    Set ai to ai plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set a_scanning to 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let a_lead_zeros be ai
    Let a_remaining be a_eff minus a_lead_zeros

    Let bj be 0
    Let b_scanning be 1
    While b_scanning is equal to 1:
        If bj is greater than or equal to b_eff:
            Set b_scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            If b is equal to 0:
                Set b_eff to 0
                Set b_scanning to 0
            Otherwise:
                Let bv be Memory.memory_get_byte(b, bj)
                If bv is equal to 0:
                    Set bj to bj plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set b_scanning to 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let b_lead_zeros be bj
    Let b_remaining be b_eff minus b_lead_zeros

    If a_remaining is less than b_remaining:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_remaining is greater than b_remaining:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let k be 0
    While k is less than a_remaining:
        Let da be Memory.memory_get_byte(a, a_lead_zeros plus k)
        Let db be Memory.memory_get_byte(b, b_lead_zeros plus k)
        If da is less than db:
            Return -1
        End If
        If da is greater than db:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Addition (magnitudes; signs handled at the call site)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "decbn_add_magnitude" takes a as Integer, a_count as Integer, b as Integer, b_count as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Adds two magnitude digit buffers and returns a fresh buffer holding
    the sum. The sum can have at most max(a_count, b_count) + 1 digits.
    The result is normalized: no leading zeros except for the canonical
    zero (a single 0 digit with count=1).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Right-to-left grade-school addition with a carry word. Operand
    digits are aligned by right-justification - we conceptually pad
    the shorter operand with leading zeros (no buffer modification
    needed, just an index check).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(a_count, b_count)). Allocates one buffer of size
    max+2 (max+1 for digits, +1 slack for downstream use).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0 and sets *out_count_ptr = 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let big_n be a_count
    If b_count is greater than big_n:
        Set big_n to b_count
    End If
    Let result_capacity be big_n plus 2
    Let result be decbn_alloc(result_capacity)
    If result is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Build digits right-to-left into a temporary array, then
    Note: compact into the result buffer in big-endian order.
    Let temp be decbn_alloc(result_capacity)
    If temp is equal to 0:
        decbn_free(result)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Let carry be 0
    Let i be 0
    Note: i counts position from least-significant end (0 = ones digit).
    While i is less than big_n:
        Let da be 0
        Let db be 0
        If i is less than a_count:
            Set da to Memory.memory_get_byte(a, a_count minus 1 minus i)
        End If
        If i is less than b_count:
            Set db to Memory.memory_get_byte(b, b_count minus 1 minus i)
        End If
        Let s be da plus db plus carry
        Set carry to s divided by 10
        Memory.memory_set_byte(temp, i, s minus (carry multiplied by 10))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let final_count be big_n
    If carry is greater than 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(temp, i, carry)
        Set final_count to final_count plus 1
    End If

    Note: Reverse temp into result.
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than final_count:
        Let v be Memory.memory_get_byte(temp, final_count minus 1 minus j)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(result, j, v)
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    decbn_free(temp)

    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, final_count)
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Process called "decbn_sub_magnitude" takes a as Integer, a_count as Integer, b as Integer, b_count as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes a - b assuming |a| >= |b|. Caller must verify ordering
    via decbn_compare_magnitude before calling. The result is
    normalized (no leading zeros) and has at most a_count digits.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Right-to-left grade-school subtraction with a borrow word.
    Strip leading zeros from the result before returning.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    If |b| > |a| the result is undefined and likely garbage. The
    caller MUST check ordering. We do not assert here because the
    routine is on the hot path of the add/sub combine step.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let temp_capacity be a_count plus 2
    Let temp be decbn_alloc(temp_capacity)
    If temp is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Let borrow be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than a_count:
        Let da be Memory.memory_get_byte(a, a_count minus 1 minus i)
        Let db be 0
        If i is less than b_count:
            Set db to Memory.memory_get_byte(b, b_count minus 1 minus i)
        End If
        Let diff be da minus db minus borrow
        If diff is less than 0:
            Set diff to diff plus 10
            Set borrow to 1
        Otherwise:
            Set borrow to 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(temp, i, diff)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Strip leading zeros (which are at the HIGH end of the temp
    Note: array, i.e. the largest indices).
    Let effective_count be a_count
    Let scan be a_count minus 1
    While scan is greater than 0:
        Let v be Memory.memory_get_byte(temp, scan)
        If v is equal to 0:
            Set effective_count to effective_count minus 1
            Set scan to scan minus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set scan to 0
        End If
    End While

    Let result be decbn_alloc(effective_count plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        decbn_free(temp)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Let j be 0
    While j is less than effective_count:
        Let v2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(temp, effective_count minus 1 minus j)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(result, j, v2)
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    decbn_free(temp)

    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, effective_count)
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Multiplication (grade-school)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "decbn_mul" takes a as Integer, a_count as Integer, b as Integer, b_count as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiplies two magnitude digit buffers; the result has at most
    a_count + b_count digits. Uses classical O(n*m) long multiplication
    in the decimal base, suitable for up to ~50-digit operands where
    Karatsuba's crossover begins; below that the constant factor of
    grade-school dominates. For Decimal64 (16 digits) and Decimal128
    (34 digits) classical is optimal.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Two-loop accumulator: for each digit of b (least-significant first)
    multiply the entire a by that digit, accumulate with carry into a
    temp buffer at position offset by the b digit's position from the
    right. Then compact and reverse into the final result.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count * b_count). For 34*34 = 1156 single-digit multiplies
    plus carries.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let total_size be a_count plus b_count plus 2
    Let temp be decbn_alloc(total_size)
    If temp is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: temp is indexed right-to-left (index 0 = ones digit).
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than b_count:
        Let bd be Memory.memory_get_byte(b, b_count minus 1 minus i)
        If bd is greater than 0:
            Let carry be 0
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than a_count:
                Let ad be Memory.memory_get_byte(a, a_count minus 1 minus j)
                Let existing be Memory.memory_get_byte(temp, i plus j)
                Let p be (ad multiplied by bd) plus existing plus carry
                Set carry to p divided by 10
                Memory.memory_set_byte(temp, i plus j, p minus (carry multiplied by 10))
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            Note: Propagate trailing carry.
            Let k be a_count
            While carry is greater than 0:
                Let existing2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(temp, i plus k)
                Let s be existing2 plus carry
                Set carry to s divided by 10
                Memory.memory_set_byte(temp, i plus k, s minus (carry multiplied by 10))
                Set k to k plus 1
            End While
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Determine effective digit count by scanning from the high end.
    Let max_pos be a_count plus b_count
    Let effective be max_pos
    While effective is greater than 1:
        Let hv be Memory.memory_get_byte(temp, effective minus 1)
        If hv is equal to 0:
            Set effective to effective minus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set effective to 0 minus effective
        End If
    End While
    If effective is less than 0:
        Set effective to 0 minus effective
    End If
    If effective is equal to 0:
        Set effective to 1
    End If

    Let result be decbn_alloc(effective plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        decbn_free(temp)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let m be 0
    While m is less than effective:
        Let v be Memory.memory_get_byte(temp, effective minus 1 minus m)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(result, m, v)
        Set m to m plus 1
    End While
    decbn_free(temp)
    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, effective)
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Division (long division)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "decbn_div_mod" takes a as Integer, a_count as Integer, b as Integer, b_count as Integer, quo_count_ptr as Integer, rem_count_ptr as Integer, rem_out_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Long division of a / b. Returns the quotient as the function return,
    the quotient's digit count via quo_count_ptr, and the remainder
    via rem_count_ptr + rem_out_ptr. The remainder buffer is allocated
    by this routine and stored at *rem_out_ptr; the caller is
    responsible for freeing both buffers via decbn_free.

    This is correctly-rounding-capable since the remainder carries
    all the rounding-decision information.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Schoolbook long division: bring down one digit at a time from a,
    maintain a running prefix, and subtract the largest multiple of b
    that fits. For each step the trial digit is at most 9; we try
    0..9 in ascending order to find the largest k such that k*b <=
    prefix. This is O(a_count * b_count * 10) per division.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Heavier than mul but acceptable for v0.0.8.5. Improvements to
    Knuth Algorithm D can come later behind a perf benchmark.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Divide by zero returns 0 quotient and 0 remainder; callers MUST
    check for cb=0 before calling.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        If quo_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(quo_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        If rem_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(rem_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        If rem_out_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(rem_out_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If b_count is equal to 1:
        Let only_digit be Memory.memory_get_byte(b, 0)
        If only_digit is equal to 0:
            If quo_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
                __store(quo_count_ptr, 0, 0)
            End If
            If rem_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
                __store(rem_count_ptr, 0, 0)
            End If
            If rem_out_ptr is not equal to 0:
                __store(rem_out_ptr, 0, 0)
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note: Quotient buffer: at most a_count digits.
    Let q_buf be decbn_alloc(a_count plus 1)
    If q_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Prefix buffer: at most b_count + 1 digits.
    Let prefix_capacity be b_count plus 2
    Let prefix_buf be decbn_alloc(prefix_capacity)
    If prefix_buf is equal to 0:
        decbn_free(q_buf)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prefix_count be 0

    Let pos be 0
    Let q_pos be 0
    Let zero_buf be decbn_alloc(1)
    If zero_buf is equal to 0:
        decbn_free(q_buf)
        decbn_free(prefix_buf)
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(zero_buf, 0, 0)

    While pos is less than a_count:
        Let next_digit be Memory.memory_get_byte(a, pos)
        Note: Append next_digit to prefix. In big-endian layout (index 0
        Note: is most significant) this is simply: write next_digit at
        Note: index prefix_count then increment prefix_count. If the
        Note: prefix is currently zero, we treat the leading zero as
        Note: dropped so we do not accumulate "00..."; the only digit
        Note: present becomes next_digit.
        If prefix_count is equal to 0:
            If next_digit is not equal to 0:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(prefix_buf, 0, next_digit)
                Set prefix_count to 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(prefix_buf, prefix_count, next_digit)
            Set prefix_count to prefix_count plus 1
        End If

        Note: Find the largest k in 0..9 such that k*b <= prefix.
        Let k be 9
        Let trial be 0
        Let trial_count be 0
        Let found be 0
        While found is equal to 0:
            Note: Build k * b: scale b by k.
            If k is equal to 0:
                Set trial to zero_buf
                Set trial_count to 1
                Set found to 1
            Otherwise:
                Let scaled_count_storage be Layout.allocate(8)
                If scaled_count_storage is equal to 0:
                    decbn_free(q_buf)
                    decbn_free(prefix_buf)
                    decbn_free(zero_buf)
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let scaled be decbn_scale_by_digit(b, b_count, k, scaled_count_storage)
                Let scaled_count be __load(scaled_count_storage, 0)
                Layout.deallocate(scaled_count_storage)
                If scaled is equal to 0:
                    decbn_free(q_buf)
                    decbn_free(prefix_buf)
                    decbn_free(zero_buf)
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let cmp be decbn_compare_magnitude(scaled, scaled_count, prefix_buf, prefix_count)
                If cmp is less than or equal to 0:
                    Set trial to scaled
                    Set trial_count to scaled_count
                    Set found to 1
                Otherwise:
                    decbn_free(scaled)
                    Set k to k minus 1
                End If
            End If
        End While

        Memory.memory_set_byte(q_buf, q_pos, k)
        Set q_pos to q_pos plus 1

        If k is greater than 0:
            Let sub_count_storage be Layout.allocate(8)
            If sub_count_storage is equal to 0:
                decbn_free(trial)
                decbn_free(q_buf)
                decbn_free(prefix_buf)
                decbn_free(zero_buf)
                Return 0
            End If
            Let new_prefix be decbn_sub_magnitude(prefix_buf, prefix_count, trial, trial_count, sub_count_storage)
            Let new_prefix_count be __load(sub_count_storage, 0)
            Layout.deallocate(sub_count_storage)
            decbn_free(trial)
            If new_prefix is equal to 0:
                decbn_free(q_buf)
                decbn_free(prefix_buf)
                decbn_free(zero_buf)
                Return 0
            End If
            Note: Copy new_prefix back into prefix_buf.
            Let n2 be 0
            While n2 is less than new_prefix_count:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(prefix_buf, n2, Memory.memory_get_byte(new_prefix, n2))
                Set n2 to n2 plus 1
            End While
            Set prefix_count to new_prefix_count
            decbn_free(new_prefix)
        End If

        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End While

    decbn_free(zero_buf)

    Note: Strip leading zeros from quotient. We keep at least one digit
    Note: so that a zero quotient is represented as a single 0.
    Let q_lead be 0
    Let scanning_zeros be 1
    While scanning_zeros is equal to 1:
        If q_lead is greater than or equal to q_pos minus 1:
            Set scanning_zeros to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let qv be Memory.memory_get_byte(q_buf, q_lead)
            If qv is equal to 0:
                Set q_lead to q_lead plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning_zeros to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Let q_final_count be q_pos minus q_lead
    Let q_final be decbn_alloc(q_final_count plus 1)
    If q_final is equal to 0:
        decbn_free(q_buf)
        decbn_free(prefix_buf)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let fi be 0
    While fi is less than q_final_count:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(q_final, fi, Memory.memory_get_byte(q_buf, q_lead plus fi))
        Set fi to fi plus 1
    End While
    decbn_free(q_buf)

    Note: Remainder is whatever remains in prefix_buf.
    Let rem be decbn_alloc(prefix_count plus 1)
    If rem is equal to 0:
        decbn_free(q_final)
        decbn_free(prefix_buf)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ri be 0
    Let rem_effective be prefix_count
    If rem_effective is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(rem, 0, 0)
        Set rem_effective to 1
    Otherwise:
        While ri is less than rem_effective:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(rem, ri, Memory.memory_get_byte(prefix_buf, ri))
            Set ri to ri plus 1
        End While
    End If
    decbn_free(prefix_buf)

    If quo_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(quo_count_ptr, 0, q_final_count)
    End If
    If rem_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(rem_count_ptr, 0, rem_effective)
    End If
    If rem_out_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(rem_out_ptr, 0, rem)
    Otherwise:
        decbn_free(rem)
    End If
    Return q_final
End Process

Process called "decbn_scale_by_digit" takes a as Integer, a_count as Integer, digit as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiplies a by a single digit (0..9). Result has at most a_count+1
    digits. Used internally by decbn_div_mod's trial-digit loop.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Standard scale-by-digit: walk right-to-left, multiply each digit
    by the scalar, propagate carry.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    digit outside 0..9 will overflow the internal carry; callers in
    this module enforce the constraint.
    @End Security_Scope

    If digit is equal to 0:
        Let zero be decbn_alloc(2)
        If zero is equal to 0:
            If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
                __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zero, 0, 0)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 1)
        End If
        Return zero
    End If
    Let temp be decbn_alloc(a_count plus 2)
    If temp is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let carry be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than a_count:
        Let ad be Memory.memory_get_byte(a, a_count minus 1 minus i)
        Let p be (ad multiplied by digit) plus carry
        Set carry to p divided by 10
        Memory.memory_set_byte(temp, i, p minus (carry multiplied by 10))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let final_count be a_count
    While carry is greater than 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(temp, i, carry minus ((carry divided by 10) multiplied by 10))
        Set carry to carry divided by 10
        Set final_count to final_count plus 1
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let result be decbn_alloc(final_count plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        decbn_free(temp)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than final_count:
        Let v be Memory.memory_get_byte(temp, final_count minus 1 minus j)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(result, j, v)
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    decbn_free(temp)
    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, final_count)
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Rounding to a specified digit count (IEEE 754-2008 Section 4.3)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "decbn_round_to_precision" takes buf as Integer, count as Integer, precision as Integer, sign as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer, exp_delta_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Rounds a digit buffer to at most 'precision' digits per the given
    IEEE 754-2008 rounding mode. The returned buffer is fresh; the
    caller must free it. The exponent delta caused by digit-shrinkage
    or carry-out is written into *exp_delta_ptr (positive means the
    exponent should increase by that amount).

    Rounding modes:
        HALF_EVEN: ties go to even last digit (default for finance).
        HALF_UP:   ties go away from zero.
        TOWARD_ZERO: truncation.
        TOWARD_POS: round up if positive sign and non-zero discarded.
        TOWARD_NEG: round up if negative sign and non-zero discarded.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. If count <= precision, return copy with exp_delta=0.
    2. Compute excess = count - precision. The first 'precision'
       digits are kept; the remaining 'excess' digits inform the
       rounding decision.
    3. Build the kept-digit buffer.
    4. Determine round_up by examining the first discarded digit
       (the rounding digit) and the sticky bit (OR of remaining
       discarded digits).
    5. If round_up, propagate +1 with carry through the kept buffer.
       A carry-out from the high digit shifts the result and bumps
       exp_delta.
    6. Set *exp_delta_ptr = excess (+ optional 1 for the carry).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(excess + precision). For typical Decimal{32,64,128} flows the
    excess is small (1-2 digits).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If buf is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        If exp_delta_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(exp_delta_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    If count is less than or equal to precision:
        If exp_delta_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(exp_delta_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Let copy be decbn_copy(buf, count)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, count)
        End If
        Return copy
    End If

    Let excess be count minus precision
    Let result be decbn_alloc(precision plus 2)
    If result is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        If exp_delta_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(exp_delta_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than precision:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(result, i, Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, i))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let rounding_digit be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, precision)
    Let sticky be 0
    Let s be precision plus 1
    While s is less than count:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, s) is not equal to 0:
            Set sticky to 1
            Set s to count
        Otherwise:
            Set s to s plus 1
        End If
    End While

    Let round_up be 0
    If rounding_mode is equal to DECBN_ROUND_HALF_EVEN:
        If rounding_digit is greater than 5:
            Set round_up to 1
        Otherwise:
            If rounding_digit is equal to 5:
                If sticky is equal to 1:
                    Set round_up to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let last_kept be Memory.memory_get_byte(result, precision minus 1)
                    If last_kept is not equal to ((last_kept divided by 2) multiplied by 2):
                        Set round_up to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If rounding_mode is equal to DECBN_ROUND_HALF_UP:
        If rounding_digit is greater than or equal to 5:
            Set round_up to 1
        End If
    End If
    If rounding_mode is equal to DECBN_ROUND_TOWARD_POS:
        If sign is equal to 0:
            If rounding_digit is greater than 0:
                Set round_up to 1
            End If
            If sticky is equal to 1:
                Set round_up to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If rounding_mode is equal to DECBN_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG:
        If sign is equal to 1:
            If rounding_digit is greater than 0:
                Set round_up to 1
            End If
            If sticky is equal to 1:
                Set round_up to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let final_precision be precision
    Let exp_delta be excess
    If round_up is equal to 1:
        Let carry be 1
        Let cp be precision minus 1
        While cp is greater than or equal to 0:
            If carry is equal to 0:
                Set cp to -1
            Otherwise:
                Let d be Memory.memory_get_byte(result, cp)
                Set d to d plus 1
                If d is equal to 10:
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(result, cp, 0)
                    Set carry to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(result, cp, d)
                    Set carry to 0
                End If
                Set cp to cp minus 1
            End If
        End While
        If carry is equal to 1:
            Note: Carry-out: shift right by one and add leading 1.
            Let r2 be precision minus 1
            While r2 is greater than or equal to 0:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(result, r2 plus 1, Memory.memory_get_byte(result, r2))
                Set r2 to r2 minus 1
            End While
            Memory.memory_set_byte(result, 0, 1)
            Set final_precision to precision plus 1
            Set exp_delta to exp_delta plus 1
        End If
    End If

    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, final_precision)
    End If
    If exp_delta_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(exp_delta_ptr, 0, exp_delta)
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Append / parse helpers (ASCII <-> digit buffer)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "decbn_from_string" takes s as Integer, start_pos as Integer, end_pos as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parses a contiguous decimal digit string from s[start_pos..end_pos)
    into a digit buffer. Non-digit bytes cause early termination (the
    out_pos in the caller's view will be the first non-digit byte).
    Used by the Decimal{32,64,128,arbitrary} from_string parsers to
    convert the digit-only portion of the input.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Walks the range, accumulating digits into a fresh buffer. Skips
    leading zeros to keep the count normalized.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single pass; allocations bounded by the digit count.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    end_pos > start_pos must hold; otherwise we return 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If s is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If end_pos is less than or equal to start_pos:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Let capacity be end_pos minus start_pos plus 1
    Let buf be decbn_alloc(capacity)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cnt be 0
    Let i be start_pos
    Let leading_zero be 1
    While i is less than end_pos:
        Let b be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, i)
        If b is less than 48:
            Set i to end_pos
        Otherwise:
            If b is greater than 57:
                Set i to end_pos
            Otherwise:
                Let digit_value be b minus 48
                If leading_zero is equal to 1:
                    If digit_value is not equal to 0:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, cnt, digit_value)
                        Set cnt to cnt plus 1
                        Set leading_zero to 0
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, cnt, digit_value)
                    Set cnt to cnt plus 1
                End If
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While
    If cnt is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, 0, 0)
        Set cnt to 1
    End If
    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, cnt)
    End If
    Return buf
End Process

Process called "decbn_write_ascii" takes buf as Integer, count as Integer, out as Integer, out_offset as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes 'count' digits from buf as ASCII characters '0'..'9' into
    out starting at out_offset. Returns the number of bytes written
    (always equal to count on success).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Add 48 to each digit and store.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(count).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller must ensure out has space for at least count bytes from
    out_offset.
    @End Security_Scope

    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let d be Memory.memory_get_byte(buf, i)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_offset plus i, d plus 48)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return count
End Process
